# SDCoreJS SDLC Agent — Cline Rules

> Cline IDE entry point. Mirrors `AGENTS.md` and `CLAUDE.md`.

This repository is an **SDLC agent** for the SDCoreJS ecosystem:
- **Backoffice portals** in Angular with `@sd-angular/core` (Core UI)
- **Backend** in NestJS + Postgres
- **Public sites** in Next.js (SSR)

## How to use this skill set

1. **Dispatch by skill description.** Skills live under `skills/<track>/*.md` with YAML frontmatter (`name`, `description`, `allowed-tools`). Match user requests against each skill's `description` and follow the matched skill's body exactly.

2. **Workflow** (per track):
   ```
   Request
     → sdcorejs-brainstorm        (optional, if scope is open-ended)
     → sdcorejs-clarify-requirements
     → sdcorejs-write-spec → sdcorejs-review-spec      (approval gate)
                           → orchestration/auto-specs   (MANDATORY)
     → sdcorejs-plan       → sdcorejs-review-plan       (approval gate)
                           → orchestration/auto-plans   (MANDATORY)
     → <track>-write-code  (orchestrator dispatches sub-skills)
     → testing/e2e/<track> → review/code/<track> → orchestration/repair-loop
     → orchestration/comment-code  (ASK gate)
     → orchestration/verify-before-done (MANDATORY)
     → orchestration/branch-ready  (branch-hygiene sweep)
     → orchestration/auto-docs + auto-task-tracker + memories (MANDATORY)
   ```

3. **Source-of-truth files** (read on demand, do NOT preload all):
   - `CLAUDE.md` / `AGENTS.md` — same content; either works as agent config
   - `skills/tracks/<track>/_refs/architecture-principles.md` — WHY-rules per track
   - `skills/shared/sdlc/_refs/<track>.md` — design-phase patterns per track

4. **Bilingual**: Vietnamese request → Vietnamese output (full diacritics for labels/messages). English → English. Permission codes + route paths stay English.

5. **Auto-docs / memories live in the TARGET project**, never in this `sdcorejs-agent` repo:
   - `<target>/.sdcorejs/docs/<track>/` — per-session summaries
   - `<target>/.sdcorejs/memories/<track>/` — durable cross-session knowledge
   - `<target>/.sdcorejs/specs/<track>/` — approved spec snapshots
   - `<target>/.sdcorejs/plans/<track>/` — approved plan snapshots
   - `<target>/.sdcorejs/tasks/<track>.md` — living TODO

